      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Another approach that can be used for everyone, would be to save a hash of the UTXO set at various points. Then you don't need to store a complete copy, but can still verify a copy someone else gives you.\r\n\r\n(Maybe there's a way to even download the copy over the network, but that risks using a lot of data before we can verify it's correct or not. There's also a risk that someone might use it for crazy UTXO lookup, or trusted sync stuff.)",
